Package com.vaadin.polymer.vaadin

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Cell
    Object referencing a cell in the grid body and its data.
    Column
    Object for controlling and accessing a column in a vaadin-grid.
    Footer
    Object for accessing and controlling footer rows.
    Header
    Object for accessing and controlling header rows.
    HeaderAndFooterCell
    Represents a grid header/footer cell configuration.
    ItemsFunction
    The grid passes a params object as the first parameter to the items
    function.
    Row
    Object referencing to a row and it’s data.
    Selection
    Object for accessing and controlling selected rows of the grid.
    SortOrder
    Object for defining the sorting order of the columns.
    VaadinComboBoxElement
    <vaadin-combo-box> is a combo box element combining a dropdown list with an
    input field for filtering the list of items.
    VaadinComboBoxLightElement
    <vaadin-combo-box-light> is a customizable version of the <vaadin-combo-box> providing
    only the dropdown functionality and leaving the input field definition to the user.
    VaadinComboBoxOverlayElement  
    VaadinComboBoxSharedStylesElement  
    VaadinContextMenuElement
    <vaadin-context-menu> is a component for contextual menus bound to UI elements.
    VaadinContextMenuOverlayElement  
    VaadinDatePickerElement
    <vaadin-date-picker> is a date selection field which includes a scrollable
    month calendar view.
    VaadinDatePickerLightElement
    <vaadin-date-picker-light> is a customizable version of the <vaadin-date-picker> providing
    only the scrollable month calendar view and leaving the input field definition to the user.
    VaadinDatePickerOverlayElement  
    VaadinDeviceDetectorElement  
    VaadinElementsComboboxComboBoxBehavior  
    VaadinElementsComboboxDropdownBehavior  
    VaadinElementsComboboxOverlayBehavior  
    VaadinElementsDatepickerDatePickerBehavior  
    VaadinGridElement
    High quality data grid for showing large amounts of tabular data.
    VaadinIconsElement
    vaadin-icons is a set of 500+ icons which can be used together with Polymer’s iron-icon component.
    VaadinInfiniteScrollerElement  
    VaadinMonthCalendarElement  
    VaadinSplitLayoutElement
    <vaadin-split-layout> is a Polymer element implementing a split layout for two
    content elements with a draggable splitter between them.
    VaadinUploadElement
    <vaadin-upload> is a Polymer element for uploading multiple files with drag and drop support.
    VaadinUploadFileElement
    <vaadin-upload-file> element represents a file in the file list of <vaadin-upload>.
